    <%# ── §1 System Overview ───────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="overview">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§1</div>
        <h2>System Overview</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="dp-audit">
        <span class="dp-ci">&#9733;</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Sovereign Logging Mandate:</strong> The System Events tab does NOT log UI
          telemetry (button clicks, field changes, dialog openings). It logs every action that
          carries <em>Administrative or Monetary Intent</em> — minting, issuance, transfers,
          burns, approvals, rejections, signature operations, batch uploads, and security alerts.
          These are permanent sovereign records. AUDIT-tier events are always visible regardless
          of severity filter setting.
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        The System Events tab is the <strong>Forensic Infrastructure Workstation</strong> of the
        bearerCORE™ CBDC platform. It provides a three-pane interface — Infrastructure Health (left),
        Live Event Stream (centre), Event Inspection &amp; Forensics (right) — through which
        System Administrators monitor node health, trace live events, investigate incidents, and
        export certified audit logs.
      </p>
      <p>
        The tab is gated behind the <code>system_admin</code> operator role. Operators with roles
        of <code>auditor</code>, <code>operator</code>, <code>viewer</code>, or <code>null</code>
        receive an "Access Restricted" modal when they attempt to navigate to the tab.
        The tab itself is hidden from the tab bar for non-admin roles via
        <code>QTabWidget::setTabVisible(6, false)</code> at application startup.
      </p>

      <h3>Key Concepts</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Concept</th><th>Definition</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Event Stream</strong></td>
            <td>The ordered, time-stamped sequence of system events emitted by all services (Rails, Qt6, DLT, HSM, Nginx). Newest events appear at the top of the table. The stream is polled every 5 seconds in live-tail mode.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Severity Levels</strong></td>
            <td>
              <span class="se-sev audit">AUDIT</span> — monetary/authority action, always visible, gold. &nbsp;
              <span class="se-sev critical">CRITICAL</span> — service failure requiring immediate action. &nbsp;
              <span class="se-sev error">ERROR</span> — recoverable failure. &nbsp;
              <span class="se-sev warn">WARN</span> — degraded state. &nbsp;
              <span class="se-sev info">INFO</span> — normal operational event.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Service Sources</strong></td>
            <td>Each event is tagged with its origin: <code>Rails</code>, <code>Qt6 Bridge</code>, <code>DLT Node</code>, <code>HSM Module</code>, <code>PostgreSQL</code>, <code>Nginx</code>, <code>SFTP</code>, <code>Sidekiq</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Event Metadata</strong></td>
            <td>Structured data attached to every event: service, timestamp, payload, environment data, and cryptographic hash. Displayed in the right pane when a row is selected.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Trace Stack</strong></td>
            <td>A captured call-path array attached to ERROR and CRITICAL events. Shows the exact method chain from error origin to service boundary. Displayed in the right pane only when the selected event has <code>severity ∈ {ERROR, CRITICAL}</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Payload Inspection</strong></td>
            <td>The raw JSON body of the request or background job that produced the event. Sensitive fields (keys, tokens) are redacted with <code>***</code> before display. The payload is stored in <code>EventMetadata.payload</code> (JSONB).</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>AUDIT Authority Signature</strong></td>
            <td>All AUDIT-tier events carry a structured prefix: <code>[ACTION: {code}] | {message}</code>. Action codes are canonical verbs: <code>EXECUTE_MINT</code>, <code>EXECUTE_ISSUE</code>, <code>EXECUTE_TRANSFER</code>, <code>EXECUTE_BURN</code>, <code>AUTHORITY_APPROVE</code>, <code>AUTHORITY_REJECT</code>, <code>AUTHORITY_SIGN</code>, <code>SECURITY_ALERT</code>, <code>EXECUTE_FREEZE</code>, <code>BATCH_OPERATION</code>.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <div class="dp-pane-grid">
        <div class="dp-pane dp-pane-left">
          <h3>Left Pane — Infrastructure Health</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Six node health cards (Rails, DLT ×2, HSM, PostgreSQL, Nginx)</li>
            <li>Status dot per card: green Active / amber Degraded / red Offline</li>
            <li>Block height, peer count, uptime, thread count per card</li>
            <li>Auto-refresh every 30 seconds via <code>GET /api/v2/health</code></li>
            <li>Performance counters: CPU, Memory, Network Latency</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-pane dp-pane-middle">
          <h3>Centre Pane — Live Event Stream</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Five-column table: Severity · Timestamp · Service · Event ID · Message</li>
            <li>Newest-first row insertion (<code>insertRow(0)</code>)</li>
            <li>Live-tail toggle button (↓ Live, green when on)</li>
            <li>Keyword search bar — filters all visible rows in real time</li>
            <li>Severity combo: All / Info+ / Errors + Audit</li>
            <li>AUDIT rows always visible regardless of filter setting</li>
            <li>Export Terminal Logs, Clear Terminal, Clear Cache buttons</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-pane dp-pane-right">
          <h3>Right Pane — Forensics &amp; Inspection</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Event Metadata panel: ID, Severity, Timestamp, Service</li>
            <li>Request Payload viewer (dark JSON pane, sensitive fields redacted)</li>
            <li>Trace Stack (errors only) — call-path array</li>
            <li>Performance Environment: Latency, CPU, Memory at event time</li>
            <li>Cryptographic Reference: manifest hash + verification status</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Severity Decision Table</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Severity</th><th>Trigger Keywords / Conditions</th><th>Color (bg / fg)</th><th>Filter Behavior</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="se-sev audit">AUDIT</span></td>
            <td><code>created cbdc</code>, <code>minted</code>, <code>printed</code>, <code>cbdc</code>, <code>burn</code>, <code>deposit</code>, <code>redeem</code>, <code>transfer</code>, <code>approved</code>, <code>rejected</code>, <code>counterfeit</code>, <code>freeze</code>, <code>ed25519</code>, <code>signature</code>, <code>batch upload</code>, <code>batch process</code>, <code>cache cleared</code>, <code>logs.txt deleted</code></td>
            <td><code>#1a1200</code> / <code>#ffd700</code></td>
            <td><strong>Always visible</strong> — bypasses severity filter. Keyword search still applies.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="se-sev critical">CRITICAL</span></td>
            <td>Service unreachable, database connection lost, HSM key failure, DLT fork detected</td>
            <td><code>#7f0000</code> / <code>#ffcdd2</code></td>
            <td>Visible in All and Errors + Audit modes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="se-sev error">ERROR</span></td>
            <td><code>error</code>, <code>failed</code>, <code>exception</code>, <code>fatal</code>, <code>crash</code></td>
            <td><code>#fce4ec</code> / <code>#b71c1c</code></td>
            <td>Visible in All and Errors + Audit modes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="se-sev warn">WARN</span></td>
            <td><code>warn</code>, <code>timeout</code>, <code>retry</code>, <code>slow</code>, <code>degraded</code></td>
            <td><code>#fff8e1</code> / <code>#e65100</code></td>
            <td>Visible in All and Info+ modes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="se-sev info">INFO</span></td>
            <td>All other messages not matched above</td>
            <td><code>#e0f7fa</code> / <code>#006064</code></td>
            <td>Visible in All mode only</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>Noise Filter — What Is NOT Logged</h3>
      <p>
        The following message patterns are discarded at the intake point in
        <code>setConsoleProcessing()</code> before any severity detection or row insertion:
      </p>
      <div class="dp-rule">
        "Send button disabled"<br>
        "Send button enabled"<br>
        "button disabled"<br>
        "Select Serial Number"<br>
        "Showing Vault Mint Dialog"<br>
        "File selection cancelled"<br>
        "Directory path:"
      </div>
    </div>

    <%# ── §2 Data Models ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="data-models">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§2</div>
        <h2>Data Models</h2>
      </div>

      <p>
        Seven models capture the full lifecycle of a system event — from raw emission through
        metadata enrichment, trace capture, node health snapshot, and cryptographic reference.
        All models link via <code>event_id</code> as the shared foreign key.
      </p>

      <h3>SystemEvent</h3>
      <p>Root record for every event. Persisted to the Rails PostgreSQL database and to the local
        <code>logs.txt</code> flat file simultaneously on every write.</p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">id</td><td class="t">uuid</td><td>Primary key</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">event_id</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Human-readable reference, e.g. <code>EVT-20260417-A3F9</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">timestamp</td><td class="t">timestamp</td><td>UTC emission time. Displayed in local timezone in the UI. Stored as UTC in PostgreSQL.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">severity</td><td class="t">enum</td><td><code>INFO</code> | <code>WARN</code> | <code>ERROR</code> | <code>CRITICAL</code> | <code>AUDIT</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">service_source</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Originating service tag: <code>Rails</code> | <code>Qt6 Bridge</code> | <code>DLT Node</code> | <code>HSM Module</code> | <code>PostgreSQL</code> | <code>Nginx</code> | <code>SFTP</code> | <code>Sidekiq</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">message</td><td class="t">text</td><td>Full event message. For AUDIT severity, includes the authority prefix: <code>[ACTION: EXECUTE_MINT] | original message</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">node_id</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Identifier of the node that emitted the event (matches <code>nodeIdentifier</code> in <code>scconfig.xml</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">correlation_id</td><td class="t">string</td><td>UUID linking events from the same logical operation (e.g. all events from a single batch mint share one <code>correlation_id</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">action_code</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Canonical action for AUDIT events: <code>EXECUTE_MINT</code>, <code>EXECUTE_ISSUE</code>, <code>EXECUTE_TRANSFER</code>, <code>EXECUTE_BURN</code>, <code>AUTHORITY_APPROVE</code>, <code>AUTHORITY_REJECT</code>, <code>AUTHORITY_SIGN</code>, <code>SECURITY_ALERT</code>, <code>EXECUTE_FREEZE</code>, <code>BATCH_OPERATION</code>, <code>AUTHORITY_ACTION</code>. Null for non-AUDIT events.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>EventMetadata</h3>
      <p>Enrichment record created asynchronously after the root event is written. Stores the full
        request context, environment snapshot, and SHA-256 content hash.</p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">id</td><td class="t">uuid</td><td>Primary key</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">system_event_id</td><td class="t">uuid FK</td><td>Parent event</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">service</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Same as <code>SystemEvent.service_source</code> — denormalized for query performance</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">timestamp</td><td class="t">timestamp</td><td>Time metadata was captured (may differ from event timestamp by milliseconds)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">payload</td><td class="t">jsonb</td><td>Raw request or job body. Sensitive fields (<code>api_auth_token</code>, private keys, passwords) are redacted with <code>***REDACTED***</code> before storage.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">environment_data</td><td class="t">jsonb</td><td>Snapshot of environment at event time: <code>{ cbdc_mode, node_id, rails_env, ruby_version, uptime_seconds }</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">cryptographic_hash</td><td class="t">string</td><td>SHA-256 hex digest of <code>message + timestamp + node_id</code>. Used for tamper detection of the event record itself.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>TraceStack</h3>
      <p>Captured only for <code>ERROR</code> and <code>CRITICAL</code> events. Contains the full
        call-path array from the error origin to the service boundary.</p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">id</td><td class="t">uuid</td><td>Primary key</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">system_event_id</td><td class="t">uuid FK</td><td>Parent event</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">trace_id</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Unique trace reference, e.g. <code>TRC-20260417-B7C1</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">stack_entries</td><td class="t">jsonb (array)</td><td>Array of <code>{ file, line, method }</code> objects in call order from outermost to error origin</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">error_origin</td><td class="t">string</td><td>The exact file:line where the exception was raised (e.g. <code>app/services/validation/ingest_service.rb:47</code>)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">call_path</td><td class="t">text</td><td>Flattened single-string representation of the full stack for log file export</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>NodeStatus</h3>
      <p>One record per monitored infrastructure node. Refreshed every 30 seconds by the Qt6 health
        polling timer via <code>GET /api/v2/health</code>. Drives the left-pane node cards.</p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">node_name</td><td class="t">string</td><td><code>rails_server</code> | <code>dlt_node_1</code> | <code>dlt_node_2</code> | <code>hsm_module</code> | <code>postgresql</code> | <code>nginx_bridge</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">status</td><td class="t">enum</td><td><code>active</code> | <code>degraded</code> | <code>offline</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">block_height</td><td class="t">integer</td><td>Current ledger block height. Proxy: <code>LedgerEvent.count</code>. Null for non-DLT nodes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">peer_count</td><td class="t">integer</td><td>Connected peers. Proxy: <code>PeerIpaddress.count</code>. Null for non-DLT nodes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">last_sync_time</td><td class="t">timestamp</td><td>Time of most recent successful health check. Drives the "Last sync" label in the node card.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">uptime_seconds</td><td class="t">integer</td><td>Rails process uptime from <code>Process.clock_gettime(Process::CLOCK_MONOTONIC)</code>. Null for external nodes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">thread_count</td><td class="t">integer</td><td>Active Puma threads (Rails). Null for external nodes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">active_key_id</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Latest <code>IssuerKey.currently_valid</code> identifier. HSM module only. Null for all other nodes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">tls_active</td><td class="t">boolean</td><td>Whether the last request to Rails arrived over TLS. Nginx/Qt6 Bridge only.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>InfrastructureHealth</h3>
      <p>Aggregated health envelope returned by <code>GET /api/v2/health</code>. Wraps individual
        NodeStatus records into a single response object consumed by the Qt6 polling timer.</p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">service_name</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Canonical node identifier — same enum as <code>NodeStatus.node_name</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">status</td><td class="t">string</td><td><code>active</code> | <code>degraded</code> | <code>offline</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">uptime</td><td class="t">string</td><td>Human-formatted uptime string: <code>"4d 2h 17m"</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">connection_state</td><td class="t">string</td><td><code>connected</code> | <code>syncing</code> | <code>disconnected</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>PerformanceMetrics</h3>
      <p>Point-in-time snapshot captured at the moment the event was emitted.
        Stored in <code>EventMetadata.environment_data</code> and displayed in the right pane.</p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">cpu_usage</td><td class="t">decimal</td><td>Percentage CPU utilization at event time. Sourced from <code>/proc/stat</code> on Linux or <code>host_cpu_usage_info()</code> via Mach API on macOS.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">memory_usage</td><td class="t">decimal</td><td>Percentage of physical RAM in use. Sourced from <code>GC.stat</code> on Ruby side; Mach memory API on Qt6 side.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">network_latency</td><td class="t">integer</td><td>Round-trip latency in milliseconds to the Rails API endpoint, measured at the time of the most recent health poll.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3>CryptographicReference</h3>
      <p>Links an event to the CBDC manifest it references, enabling cross-tab forensic correlation
        between the System Events log and the Validation Desk / Audit &amp; Reports tab.</p>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">system_event_id</td><td class="t">uuid FK</td><td>Parent event</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">manifest_hash</td><td class="t">string</td><td>SHA-256 hex digest of the CBDC batch manifest. Populated for AUDIT events with <code>action_code ∈ {EXECUTE_MINT, EXECUTE_ISSUE, BATCH_OPERATION}</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">verification_status</td><td class="t">enum</td><td><code>verified</code> | <code>unverified</code> | <code>tampered</code> | <code>pending</code>. Set to <code>pending</code> at creation; updated by <code>Validation::SignatureVerificationService</code> when it runs.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>
    </div>

