        status = "offline"                                       →  red dot    (#ef5350)<br>
        API request timeout or network error                     →  red dot    (#ef5350), card label "Offline"
      </div>

      <h3>D. Node Details — Data Source &amp; Refresh</h3>
      <p>
        The Qt6 client fires <code>refreshNodeHealth()</code> on tab show and then every 30 seconds
        via <code>m_healthTimer</code>. Each call issues a single
        <code>GET {F5URL}/api/v2/health</code> request with the Bearer token.
        The response JSON is parsed in <code>applyNodeHealthJson()</code> which
        updates each card's label and dot color in place. No page reload occurs.
      </p>
      <div class="dp-callout dp-warn">
        <span class="dp-ci">⚠</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Brace initialization required:</strong> the <code>QNetworkRequest</code> object
          inside <code>refreshNodeHealth()</code> must be initialized with braces —
          <code>QNetworkRequest req{QUrl(url)};</code> — not parentheses. The parenthesis form
          triggers the C++ most-vexing-parse and is silently mis-compiled as a function declaration,
          causing all subsequent member calls to fail at compile time.
        </div>
      </div>

