      <h3>D. Row Insertion &amp; Ordering</h3>
      <p>
        New events are always inserted at row index 0 (<code>insertRow(0)</code>), so the newest
        event is at the top of the table. This is the inverse of a traditional append-at-bottom
        log. The table uses <code>QTableWidget</code> with <code>setEditTriggers(NoEditTriggers)</code>
        and <code>setSelectionBehavior(SelectRows)</code>.
      </p>

      <h3>E. Filter Logic — Combined Severity + Keyword</h3>
      <p><code>applySysEventFilter()</code> is called whenever the severity combo or the search bar
        changes. It iterates every row in the table:</p>
      <div class="dp-rule">
        For each row:<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;severity = row[col_0].data(Qt::UserRole)  // stored as plain string<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;message  = row[col_4].text()<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;eid      = row[col_3].text()<br>
        <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;// Severity gate — AUDIT always passes<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;severityOk = (severity == "AUDIT")<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;if !severityOk:<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if combo == "All":            severityOk = true<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if combo == "Info+":          severityOk = severity ∈ {INFO, WARN, ERROR, CRITICAL, AUDIT}<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if combo == "Errors + Audit": severityOk = severity ∈ {ERROR, CRITICAL}<br>
        <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;// Keyword gate<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;searchOk = searchBar.text().isEmpty() OR<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;message.contains(needle, CaseInsensitive) OR<br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;eid.contains(needle, CaseInsensitive)<br>
        <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;row.setHidden(!(severityOk AND searchOk))
      </div>

      <h3>F. Row Click — Right Pane Loading</h3>
      <p>
        <code>QTableWidget::itemSelectionChanged</code> triggers <code>onSysEventRowSelected()</code>.
        The selected row's <code>event_id</code> (column 3) is extracted and passed to
        <code>GET {F5URL}/api/v2/system_events/{event_id}</code>. The response populates:
      </p>
      <ul style="padding-left:20px;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:2.1;">
        <li>Event Metadata panel (Event ID, Severity, Timestamp, Service)</li>
        <li>Request Payload dark JSON viewer</li>
        <li>Trace Stack panel — shown only if <code>severity ∈ {ERROR, CRITICAL}</code> and <code>trace_stack</code> key present</li>
        <li>Performance Environment (Latency, CPU, Memory) — Phase 2; shows "—" until implemented</li>
        <li>Cryptographic Reference (manifest hash + verification status)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>G. AUDIT Structured Event Emission</h3>
      <p>
        Monetary and authority controllers call <code>appendAuditEvent()</code> directly rather
        than routing through <code>setConsoleProcessing()</code>. This function constructs the
        canonical authority-signature format and writes to both the in-memory table and the
        persistent log file:
      </p>
      <div class="dp-rule">
        appendAuditEvent(action, entity, detail, refHash)<br>
        <br>
        → message = "[ACTION: {action}] | [Entity: {entity}] | [Detail: {detail}]"<br>
        → if refHash not empty: message += " | [Ref: {refHash}]"<br>
        → service = detect from action prefix (EXECUTE_* → Qt6 Bridge, AUTHORITY_* → Rails)<br>
        → appendSysEventRow("AUDIT", service, message)
      </div>

      <h3>H. Action Code Mapping</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Action Code</th><th>Trigger Keywords</th><th>Service Tag</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="f">EXECUTE_MINT</td><td><code>created cbdc</code>, <code>minted</code></td><td>Qt6 Bridge</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">EXECUTE_ISSUE</td><td><code>printed</code>, <code>cbdc</code> + <code>issu</code></td><td>Qt6 Bridge</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">EXECUTE_TRANSFER</td><td><code>transfer</code>, <code>deliver</code>, <code>sent</code>, <code>received</code></td><td>Qt6 Bridge</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">EXECUTE_BURN</td><td><code>burn</code>, <code>redeemed</code>, <code>destroyed</code></td><td>Rails</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">AUTHORITY_APPROVE</td><td><code>approved</code></td><td>Rails</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">AUTHORITY_REJECT</td><td><code>rejected</code>, <code>denied</code></td><td>Rails</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">AUTHORITY_SIGN</td><td><code>ed25519</code>, <code>signature</code>, <code>signed</code></td><td>HSM Module</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">SECURITY_ALERT</td><td><code>counterfeit</code>, <code>tamper</code>, <code>invalid sig</code>, <code>fraud</code></td><td>Rails</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">EXECUTE_FREEZE</td><td><code>freeze</code>, <code>frozen</code></td><td>Rails</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">BATCH_OPERATION</td><td><code>batch upload</code>, <code>batch process</code></td><td>Sidekiq</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="f">AUTHORITY_ACTION</td><td>(fallback — no keyword matched)</td><td>Rails</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>
    </div>

    <%# ── §5 Right Pane ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
    <div class="dp-section" id="right-pane">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§5</div>
        <h2>Right Pane — Event Inspection &amp; Forensics</h2>
      </div>

      <p>
        The right pane is divided into five vertically stacked sub-panels inside a scroll area.
        All sub-panels are empty ("—") until a row is selected in the event stream table.
        When a row is selected, a single <code>GET /api/v2/system_events/{event_id}</code>
        request retrieves the full event object and populates all sub-panels simultaneously.
      </p>

      <h3>A. Event Metadata Panel</h3>

      <div class="se-meta-card">
        <div class="se-meta-card-head">Event Metadata</div>
        <div class="se-meta-card-body">
          <div class="se-meta-row"><span class="se-meta-lbl">Event ID</span><span class="se-meta-val">EVT-20260417-A3F9</span></div>
          <div class="se-meta-row"><span class="se-meta-lbl">Severity</span><span class="se-meta-val"><span class="se-sev audit">AUDIT</span></span></div>
          <div class="se-meta-row"><span class="se-meta-lbl">Timestamp</span><span class="se-meta-val">2026-04-17 09:14:22.441 UTC</span></div>
          <div class="se-meta-row"><span class="se-meta-lbl">Service</span><span class="se-meta-val">Qt6 Bridge</span></div>
          <div class="se-meta-row"><span class="se-meta-lbl">Node ID</span><span class="se-meta-val">N9F531B1F55</span></div>
          <div class="se-meta-row"><span class="se-meta-lbl">Correlation</span><span class="se-meta-val">corr-20260417-B-0042</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Source of Truth</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Event ID</strong></td><td><code>SystemEvent.event_id</code></td><td>Human-readable reference used for cross-tab correlation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Severity</strong></td><td><code>SystemEvent.severity</code></td><td>Rendered as colored chip — same style as table column</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Timestamp</strong></td><td><code>SystemEvent.timestamp</code></td><td>Full ISO 8601 with milliseconds and explicit UTC label</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Service</strong></td><td><code>SystemEvent.service_source</code></td><td>Canonical service tag string</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Node ID</strong></td><td><code>SystemEvent.node_id</code></td><td>The <code>nodeIdentifier</code> from the emitting installation's <code>scconfig.xml</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Correlation ID</strong></td><td><code>SystemEvent.correlation_id</code></td><td>Links all events from the same logical operation. Clicking it opens a filtered view of the event stream showing only events with the same correlation ID.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

